990
01:13:06,311 --> 01:13:09,230
Then why do Roger and Chip
have the money?

991
01:13:09,314 --> 01:13:11,691
Roger and Chip?

992
01:13:14,694 --> 01:13:18,531
Stop! Don't shoot!
They're stupid and confused!

993
01:13:18,615 --> 01:13:21,034
Position! Move out!

994
01:13:21,117 --> 01:13:23,536
-l'm going in.
-Come on!

995
01:13:23,995 --> 01:13:25,747
l can't believe it.

996
01:13:25,955 --> 01:13:31,169
l can't believe Chip shafted me.

997
01:13:31,753 --> 01:13:33,338
l can't believe you came through.

998
01:13:33,421 --> 01:13:35,006
Beaver team, move in! Go!

999
01:13:39,302 --> 01:13:41,220
lt's like an army out there.

1000
01:13:42,513 --> 01:13:45,808
l'm on parole for mail fraud. l gotta hide.

1001
01:13:52,690 --> 01:13:54,734
-How'd you get in there, man?
-l mean...

1002
01:13:54,817 --> 01:13:56,694
-Come on, Grover!
-...l...

1003
01:13:56,778 --> 01:14:01,532
...took care of all of Chip's gambling debts.

1004
01:14:02,116 --> 01:14:05,828
l paid for all his methadone treatments.

1005
01:14:07,455 --> 01:14:09,832
l guess we both got the big screw.

1006
01:14:11,292 --> 01:14:13,294
Come on, Grover!

1007
01:14:14,337 --> 01:14:16,798
Don't move! Hayes and Fillmore...

1008
01:14:16,881 --> 01:14:20,385
...you're under arrest, again,
for the abduction of Virginia Crock.

1009
01:14:20,468 --> 01:14:22,762
And this time, it's gonna stick!

1010
01:14:24,931 --> 01:14:27,266
You clod.

1011
01:14:27,725 --> 01:14:30,228
They didn't kidnap me.

1012
01:14:30,311 --> 01:14:32,855
They rescued me.

1013
01:14:33,273 --> 01:14:37,735
lf Willard hadn't shown up,
l'd be dead and buried in this hellhole!

1014
01:14:38,236 --> 01:14:41,864
l don't understand.
Then who's the kidnapper?

1015
01:14:46,452 --> 01:14:49,372
First, l wanna upgrade the assembly line.

1016
01:14:49,455 --> 01:14:52,208
Toss out minced meat.

1017
01:14:52,333 --> 01:14:54,252
Bring in vanilla custard.

1018
01:14:56,170 --> 01:14:58,798
Then, l'm gonna mix
strawberry into the rhubarb.

1019
01:15:03,261 --> 01:15:05,805
Freeze! You're under arrest.

1020
01:15:07,307 --> 01:15:08,725
Chip Oswald...

1021
01:15:08,808 --> 01:15:12,854
...you are under arrest for the kidnappings
of Willard Fillmore and Virginia Crock.

1022
01:15:12,937 --> 01:15:16,399
That is ridiculous! How dare you!

1023
01:15:16,566 --> 01:15:19,027
l demand you leave my house!

1024
01:15:25,283 --> 01:15:27,619
Put on your pants. You're going to jail.

1025
01:15:27,994 --> 01:15:30,371
All right, let's get them hands
behind your back.

1026
01:15:31,623 --> 01:15:34,334
Oh, my God! lt's the new Village People.

1027
01:15:35,376 --> 01:15:37,462
-You're all crazy!
-Put down that gun!

1028
01:15:37,545 --> 01:15:40,298
-l'm not going back to prison!
-What do you mean...

1029
01:15:40,381 --> 01:15:42,008
-...''back''?
-Up yours!

1030
01:15:42,091 --> 01:15:46,721
l've got nothing from all of those years
of suffering, working for you!

1031
01:15:46,804 --> 01:15:49,098
-Nobody does.
-Stay out of this!

1032
01:15:50,099 --> 01:15:52,185
l'll see you all in hell!

1033
01:15:52,727 --> 01:15:55,772
l'll slice you and l'll dice you...

1034
01:15:55,855 --> 01:15:58,775
...and l'll bake you all into meat pies!

1035
01:16:06,658 --> 01:16:09,327
Well, it's an ugly ending,
but the case is solved.

1036
01:16:09,535 --> 01:16:12,288
l knew he was the kidnapper
the whole time.

1037
01:16:12,497 --> 01:16:15,667
Never trust a black man named Chip.

1038
01:16:22,465 --> 01:16:24,759
This is so beautiful.

1039
01:16:25,593 --> 01:16:28,680
-l could spend the rest of my life here.
-Yeah.

1040
01:16:28,763 --> 01:16:31,808
And we found a place
where almost everyone speaks English.

1041
01:16:43,069 --> 01:16:45,488
There's my juicy, succulent chicken.
Come here.

1042
01:16:46,322 --> 01:16:48,866
-How's business, baby?
-Great, Rusty.

1043
01:16:48,950 --> 01:16:50,910
You guys got a package.

1044
01:16:53,955 --> 01:16:55,039
Look.

1045
01:16:55,456 --> 01:16:57,041
lt's from Miss Crock.

1046
01:16:57,667 --> 01:16:59,502
What did she send?

1047
01:17:02,964 --> 01:17:06,634
-Check it out. lt's an Armani suit.
-And there's a letter.

1048
01:17:10,930 --> 01:17:15,184
''Dear Willard, I hope you're enjoying
your retirement money.

1049
01:17:15,268 --> 01:17:19,606
''Here's a suityou can wear
when you graduate from U.S.C.

1050
01:17:19,939 --> 01:17:23,651
''Back in Pittsburgh,
I decided not to sell the company.

1051
01:17:23,735 --> 01:17:27,614
''And I have a new man in my life.

1052
01:17:28,364 --> 01:17:30,408
''Grover's quite special.

1053
01:17:31,159 --> 01:17:35,121
''He's a little slow,
but he does what he's told.

1054
01:17:35,455 --> 01:17:38,708
''So, thanks again forintroducing us.

1055
01:17:39,083 --> 01:17:42,003
''Your everlasting friend, Virginia.''

